statement.p:
Compute the products.

5(-4)

\dfrac{-3}{4} \cdot \dfrac{1}{2}

(-3)(-3)

\dfrac{-5}{3} \cdot \dfrac{-3}{10}

Compute the quotients.

\dfrac{-25}{-5}

\dfrac{32}{-8}

-27 \div 9

-42 \div (-7)

Find the quotient if it exists.

\dfrac{0}{18}

\dfrac{13}{0}

-9 \div 0

0 \div (-2)
